comments.content: Osteoblasts are specialized, terminally differentiated cell of mesenchymal origin. They create dense, crosslinked collagen and also specialized proteins, including osteocalcin and osteopontin. This pathway illustrates various signaling pathways in osteoblasts relevant to collagen and protein production.
This pathway was inferred from Homo sapiens pathway [http://www.wikipathways.org/index.php?title=Pathway:WP322&oldid=21357 WP322(r21357)] with a 82% conversion rate.
